{"entityMap":{},"blocks":[{"key":"csurm","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b0aif","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8kjfj","text":"1. strategy to follow: keep it simple and cut to the chase.\n","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":21,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f7mei","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cmmlh","text":"2. How: to be able to get my message across in simple words means I have a good understand about it at the first place. So I need to walk through, 1) to be clear about what do I want, 2) my suggestions about how we can make it,  3) find the most simple language which is sufficent to convey your ideas, 4) to do it with the help of figures (it works on me) or others.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":6,"style":"BOLD"},{"offset":120,"length":2,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"co8c6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ekctt","text":"     Before communication happens, preparation is necessary. I cannot make yourself understood while I do not understand it myself.  So I can make it simple.\n","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":11,"style":"BOLD"},{"offset":138,"length":3,"style":"BOLD"},{"offset":138,"length":3,"style":"ITALIC"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bs7c5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8273l","text":"     While communication, keep it simple. So the other part can get it more than not. Human brain can only handle limited bits of information at given time (Csikszentmihalyi, M. Flow. 1990.), do not expect others to get all you say, expecially when the message is a load of jam. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":10,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"df6i9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7k7k0","text":"3. How to talk as a leader: be assertive, provocative, clear and simple.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":6,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"69req","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cl865","text":"4. What kind of a leader am I? ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":3,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8i929","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1g3n","text":"     I prefer my office is more of demoncracy. I do not like to direct over others. Suggestion is only I give, I give no orders. One can doubt about everything in my office. I belive the best relationship between a leader and it ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2rdij","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"68vim","text":"5. What are my leadership objectives?","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":2,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9pv0p","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"77cta","text":"6. How do I take advantage of my strong points and minimize my weaker points in communicating with others?","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":2,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}]}